<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-385-966  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 385 966.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Weekly  April 26 1990 n1211 p25(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>The friendly face of the industry. (computer industry)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Vowler, Julia.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The National Online Animal History (Noah) database is an exampleof how the computer industry can assist environmentalist groups intheir efforts to preserve endangered species.andP;  Noah is a databasethat provides a profile of the population of endangered species inzoos in Great Britain.andP;  It is sent to the International SpecialInformation System (Isis) where it is combined with similarinformation from around the world.andP;  The computer industry alsodonates computer hardware and software to environmentalist groupsthough groups such as Greenpeace refuse to accept donations on asponsorship basis.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer IndustryEnvironmental ProtectionData BasesInformation Resources ManagementGreenpeaceOn-Line.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>